WEBVTT

00:12.946 --> 00:15.249
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:15.282 --> 00:17.050
MAMA,
MOMMY'S TRYING TO TALK.

00:18.485 --> 00:19.853
Nancy: IT'S FOR YOU.

00:19.887 --> 00:22.022
TO GROW AND TO DO
WHAT YOU LOVE.

00:23.490 --> 00:25.058
IT'S GREAT.

00:25.092 --> 00:27.160
UM...ANDY...

00:27.194 --> 00:30.464
YOU'RE A MAN OF BIG IDEAS.

00:30.497 --> 00:31.598
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

00:31.632 --> 00:32.666
I WANT MY SON.

00:32.699 --> 00:34.201
I'VE BEEN INSIDE YOU.

00:34.234 --> 00:36.069
GETTING STEVIE IS NOT GONNA BE
THE ANSWER TO YOUR PROBLEMS

00:36.103 --> 00:37.704
THE SPIRIT OF COMPROMISE.

00:37.738 --> 00:41.475
EVERYONE'S A LITTLE HAPPY,
EVERYONE'S A LITTLE MISERABLE.

00:41.508 --> 00:42.442
IT'S FAMILY.

00:42.476 --> 00:43.944
Man: CADETS!

00:43.977 --> 00:46.213
WHEN YOU GRADUATE
FROM THIS POLICE ACADEMY,

00:46.246 --> 00:48.682
YOU WILL BE THE FIRST LINE
OF DEFENSE.

00:48.715 --> 00:51.952
Nancy: WE CELEBRATE THE CLOSING
OF ESCROW ON THIS,

00:51.985 --> 00:54.588
THE BOTWIN‐PRICE‐GRAY
FAMILY COMPOUND,

00:54.621 --> 00:58.292
WITH SIGNIFICANT CONTRIBUTIONS
FROM THE WILSON FUND.

00:58.325 --> 00:59.826
CFO?

00:59.860 --> 01:01.161
THAT'S A PROMOTION,
RIGHT?

01:01.195 --> 01:03.964
YOU ARE GONNA HAVE
SO MUCH MONEY.

01:03.997 --> 01:05.832
AN EXPERIMENT, TO BE SURE,

01:05.866 --> 01:08.068
BUT REALLY...
THE ONLY SOLUTION.

01:10.003 --> 01:11.872
MAY WE NOT KILL ONE ANOTHER?

01:11.905 --> 01:13.640
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:17.678 --> 01:18.712
Shayla!

01:18.745 --> 01:20.047
I SWEAR TO GOD.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.348
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:21.381 --> 01:24.718
[ LAUGHTER ]

01:24.751 --> 01:27.454
WHOO!

01:30.557 --> 01:31.758
[ GUNSHOT ]

01:37.331 --> 01:40.167
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:40.200 --> 01:42.836
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES
MADE OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:42.870 --> 01:45.405
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:45.439 --> 01:47.975
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ALL THE SAME ♪♪

01:48.008 --> 01:50.444
♪♪ THERE'S A GREEN ONE
AND A PINK ONE ♪♪

01:50.477 --> 01:53.247
♪♪ AND A BLUE ONE
AND A YELLOW ONE ♪♪

01:53.280 --> 01:55.949
♪♪ AND THEY'RE ALL MADE
OUT OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:55.983 --> 01:58.986
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK
JUST THE SAME ♪♪

02:01.822 --> 02:04.758
♪♪ AND THE PEOPLE IN THE HOUSES ♪♪

02:04.791 --> 02:07.194
♪♪ ALL WENT TO THE UNIVERSITY ♪♪

02:07.227 --> 02:09.863
♪♪ WHERE THEY WERE PUT IN BOXES ♪♪

02:09.897 --> 02:12.466
♪♪ AND THEY CAME OUT
ALL THE SAME ♪♪

02:12.499 --> 02:15.135
♪♪ AND THERE'S DOCTORS
AND LAWYERS ♪♪

02:15.169 --> 02:18.172
♪♪ AND BUSINESS EXECUTIVES ♪♪

02:18.205 --> 02:20.440
♪♪ AND THEY'RE ALL MADE
OUT OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

02:20.474 --> 02:25.412
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK
JUST THE SAME ♪♪

02:30.651 --> 02:34.054
[ HEAVY BREATHING ]

02:34.087 --> 02:36.390
[ Muffled ] NANCY? OHH, OHH.
OH, JESUS. PANTS?

02:36.423 --> 02:39.459
Nancy: [ Muffled ] I SHOULD
HAVE USED THE PLASTIC GLASSES,

02:39.493 --> 02:41.662
BUT WINE ALWAYS
TASTES BETTER IN GLASS.

02:41.695 --> 02:42.829
DON'T YOU THINK?

02:42.863 --> 02:44.531
IS EVERYONE WEARING SHOES?

02:44.565 --> 02:45.699
SILAS, CALL 911.

02:45.732 --> 02:46.533
SILAS!

02:46.567 --> 02:47.901
ZAPATOS. ZAPPOS.

02:47.935 --> 02:49.970
DO YOU THINK THAT'S WHY
THEY CALL IT ZAPPOS?

02:50.003 --> 02:52.506
BECAUSE "SHOES" IN SPANISH
IS "ZAPATOS."

02:52.539 --> 02:56.009
JESUS. DON'T MOVE.
NO, IT'S OKAY.
I'M WEARING SANDALS FROM ZAPPOS.

02:56.043 --> 02:58.345
SILAS, TAKE OUT YOUR PHONE
AND DIAL!

02:58.378 --> 03:00.380
I SAID NO PHONES
AT THE TABLE.

03:00.414 --> 03:02.382
WHAT'S THAT NOISE?
HOLY SHIT.

03:02.416 --> 03:05.419
MY NOSE IS TINGLING.
WOULD YOU HELP ME UP, ANDY?

03:05.452 --> 03:08.856
UM, I THINK YOU SHOULD STAY
RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE.
WHY?

03:08.889 --> 03:12.492
Silas: [ Muffled ]
SHE'S BEEN SHOT. M‐MY MOM'S
BEEN SHOT IN THE HEAD.

03:12.526 --> 03:13.627
WHAT? WHOSE MOM?

03:16.630 --> 03:17.965
SHAYLA, DON'T LOOK.

03:17.998 --> 03:20.033
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

03:20.067 --> 03:22.102
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

03:24.705 --> 03:28.075
OH, MOTHERFUCKER!

03:35.449 --> 03:37.618
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

03:41.788 --> 03:43.724
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

03:47.160 --> 03:49.863
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

03:49.897 --> 03:51.865
[ SIREN WAILING ]

03:51.899 --> 03:53.734
AAH!

03:55.736 --> 03:57.437
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

03:59.640 --> 04:00.841
DO YOU KNOW YOUR NAME?

04:00.874 --> 04:02.943
I DO.
I KNOW MY NAME.

04:02.976 --> 04:04.311
NANCY BOTWIN.
I'M NOT ASKING YOU.

04:04.344 --> 04:05.679
I'M ASKING HER.
I'M ASSESSING.

04:05.712 --> 04:07.080
OH. SORRY.
OH.

04:07.114 --> 04:09.616
NANCY, HOW MANY FINGERS
AM I HOLDING UP?

04:09.650 --> 04:11.418
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

04:11.451 --> 04:12.586
OVER HERE.

04:12.619 --> 04:15.822
THREE ‐‐ THREE VERY LONG,
ELEGANT FINGERS.

04:15.856 --> 04:18.792
DO YOU
PLAY THE PIANO?
NO, I DON'T.

04:18.825 --> 04:22.229
DO YOU HAVE
A VERY HAPPY GIRLFRIEND?
LET'S LET HIM ASK THE QUESTIONS,
OKAY, MOM?

04:22.262 --> 04:24.464
IT'S OKAY.
I JUST NEED TO KEEP HER TALKING.

04:24.498 --> 04:26.400
BUT YOU'RE
TRYING TO ASSESS.
HEY, DON'T TELL ME
HOW TO DO MY JOB, OKAY?

04:26.433 --> 04:29.369
DON'T SNAP AT MY KID,
LONG‐FINGER MAN. [ CHUCKLES ]

04:29.403 --> 04:32.005
LONG FINGERS SNAPPED.
[ LAUGHS ]

04:32.039 --> 04:33.874
NANCY, DO YOU KNOW
WHAT YEAR IT IS?

04:33.907 --> 04:35.909
YOU DON'T KNOW?
DOOMSDAY IS COMING.

04:35.943 --> 04:37.110
NOT REALLY, THOUGH.

04:37.144 --> 04:39.713
YOU STILL HAVEN'T
ANSWERED THE QUESTION, MOM.

04:39.746 --> 04:41.648
OH, RIGHT. UH,
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

04:41.682 --> 04:42.850
MIKE.
MIKE.

04:42.883 --> 04:44.518
YOU CAN
CALL ME NANCY.

04:44.551 --> 04:46.153
NANCY, DO YOU KNOW
WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU?

04:46.186 --> 04:47.788
YEAH.
I BROKE A GLASS.

04:47.821 --> 04:49.056
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

04:49.089 --> 04:51.191
NANCY, CAN YOU COUNT BACK
FROM 100 BY 7s FOR ME?

04:51.225 --> 04:55.429
UH, I ‐‐ I'M SO BAD
AT MATH.

04:55.462 --> 04:58.165
I'M REALLY GOOD AT BOGGLE,
THOUGH.

04:58.198 --> 05:01.535
ON A FIVE‐BY‐FIVE,
I ONCE SPELLED "PILSNERS,"

05:01.568 --> 05:02.803
LIKE THE BEERS.

05:02.836 --> 05:05.205
NINE LETTERS,
MOTHERFUCKERS.

05:05.239 --> 05:06.807
ALL RIGHT, NANCY, WE'RE ABOUT
TO GET TO THE HOSPITAL NOW.

05:06.840 --> 05:08.976
OH, 'CAUSE I'VE BEEN
SHOT IN THE HEAD.

05:09.009 --> 05:10.944
'CAUSE YOU'VE BEEN
SHOT IN THE HEAD.

05:10.978 --> 05:12.880
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]
MOTHERFUCKER.

05:12.913 --> 05:16.483
I'M JUST GONNA
CLOSE MY EYES. IS THAT OKAY?

05:16.517 --> 05:19.720
NANCY, I NEED YOU TO
KEEP TALKING TO ME, SWEETHEART.
OKAY.

05:19.753 --> 05:21.455
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
NANCY? HEY.

05:21.488 --> 05:23.357
NANCY!
MOM? MOM?

05:23.390 --> 05:24.224
MOM!

05:24.258 --> 05:24.925
MOM!

05:24.958 --> 05:26.894
MOM!

05:26.927 --> 05:28.962
[ Ringing ]

05:28.996 --> 05:30.731
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

05:32.199 --> 05:33.700
WHAT THE FUCK?
ANDY, LET'S GO!

05:33.734 --> 05:35.068
SHUT UP, JILL.

05:35.102 --> 05:38.138
SHUT YOUR MOUTH AND SHUT IT
AND SHUT UP AND SHUT UP!

05:38.172 --> 05:39.439
OKAY, COME ON.
WE'RE LEAVING.

05:39.473 --> 05:41.074
SHE ASKED ME TO PACK THINGS
FOR HER.

05:41.108 --> 05:42.943
THOSE WERE HER LAST WORDS ‐‐
"PACK ME SOME STUFF."

05:42.976 --> 05:45.312
ANDY, SHE DOESN'T NEED
A SILK CAMISOLE AND A THONG.

05:45.345 --> 05:47.281
THERE WAS BLOOD
ALL OVER HER.

05:47.314 --> 05:48.649
[ SIGHS ]

05:48.682 --> 05:50.784
THEY'LL CLEAN HER UP.

05:50.817 --> 05:53.020
THEY'LL PUT HER
IN A HOSPITAL GOWN.

05:53.053 --> 05:54.054
LET'S GO.

05:54.087 --> 05:55.756
LATER YOU CAN
GO THROUGH HER UNDERWEAR

05:55.789 --> 05:56.890
WHILE I GO THROUGH
HER JEWELRY.

05:56.924 --> 05:58.625
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

05:58.659 --> 06:00.093
I'M DARK AND DRY
IN A CRISIS.

06:00.127 --> 06:02.229
YOU CAN'T HOLD IT AGAINST ME.
WE ALL HAVE OUR WAYS.

06:02.262 --> 06:03.397
Doug:
HEY. ARE WE GOING?

06:03.430 --> 06:06.066
I'D KIND OF LIKE
TO GET THE FUCK OUT OF HERE.

06:06.099 --> 06:07.835
WHERE'S SHANE?
HE TOOK OFF
INTO THE WOODS.

06:07.868 --> 06:09.036
HE RAN AFTER THE SHOOTER.

06:09.069 --> 06:11.638
FUCK.
THAT KID'S GOT BALLS.
OR DID.

06:11.672 --> 06:12.706
THEY MIGHT BE
SHOT OFF BY NOW.

06:12.739 --> 06:15.342
YOU ARE BAD PEOPLE.

06:15.375 --> 06:17.077
LISTEN, THE MEXICAN KID
IS HIDING IN THE PANTRY.

06:17.110 --> 06:18.312
I REALLY THINK
WE SHOULD LEAVE.

06:18.345 --> 06:21.014
OKAY.
ALL THE ESSENTIALS.

06:21.048 --> 06:22.282
HERE WE GO.

06:22.316 --> 06:23.283
JILL?

06:25.552 --> 06:26.653
WHAT IF SHE DIES?

06:26.687 --> 06:28.255
SHE'S NOT GONNA DIE,
ANDY.

06:28.288 --> 06:29.289
WHY NOT?

06:29.323 --> 06:31.191
BECAUSE
THERE IS NO GOD.

06:37.865 --> 06:39.499
Whimsy: WHAT DO YOU SEE,
PILL‐PILL?

06:39.533 --> 06:41.201
Phillip:
I SEE A MESS.

06:41.235 --> 06:43.003
OH,
I'M NOT SURPRISED.

06:43.036 --> 06:45.372
THEY SEEM LIKE
THE MESSY TYPES.

06:45.405 --> 06:47.140
[ PANTING ]

06:47.174 --> 06:48.976
OH,
I DIDN'T SEE YOU THERE.

06:49.009 --> 06:50.511
WE'RE YOUR NEIGHBORS,

06:50.544 --> 06:53.480
THE ARDMORES ‐‐
PHILLIP AND WHIMSY.

06:53.514 --> 06:55.716
I THINK YOU NEED
TO CLIMB BACK DOWN YOUR LADDER.

06:55.749 --> 06:57.150
WHEN THE BRYSONS
LIVED HERE,

06:57.184 --> 06:59.720
THEY HAD AN EYESORE
OF A PLAY STRUCTURE

06:59.753 --> 07:01.722
RIGHT UP AGAINST
THE PROPERTY LINE.

07:01.755 --> 07:05.859
THEIR CHILDREN USED TO CLIMB UP
AND PEE INTO OUR YARD.

07:05.893 --> 07:07.794
I GOT THEM WITH A HOSE

07:07.828 --> 07:10.531
AND ONCE WITH A FIRE
EXTINGUISHER

07:10.564 --> 07:11.865
AND ONCE WITH BEES.

07:11.899 --> 07:13.133
ASK HIM ABOUT THE RUCKUS.

07:13.166 --> 07:15.469
OH, RIGHT.
WHAT WAS ALL THE RUCKUS?

07:15.502 --> 07:16.336
MY MOTHER GOT HURT.

07:16.370 --> 07:18.705
WE LIVE IN AN ENCLAVE,
YOU KNOW.

07:18.739 --> 07:20.073
THIS IS AN ENCLAVE.

07:20.107 --> 07:22.075
WE TRY TO KEEP
THE NOISE LEVEL

07:22.109 --> 07:24.344
DOWN TO A CIVILIZED LEVEL
OF NOISE.

07:24.378 --> 07:26.547
[ SIRENS WAILING ]
SORRY IF WE DISTURBED YOU.

07:26.580 --> 07:28.882
I WAS CHECKING THE VOLE TRAPS,
AND I HEARD A BANG.

07:28.916 --> 07:30.851
WHAT WAS THAT BANG?
IT WAS AN AWFUL BANG.

07:30.884 --> 07:31.952
[ WAILING STOPS ]
IT WAS A GUNSHOT.

07:31.985 --> 07:33.687
GUNSHOT?!

07:33.720 --> 07:35.756
WELL,
THAT'S SIMPLY UNACCEPTABLE.

07:35.789 --> 07:37.157
THOSE ARE NOT
HUNTING WOODS.

07:37.191 --> 07:38.725
THOSE ARE STROLLING WOODS.

07:38.759 --> 07:41.461
O.S. POLICE! FREEZE!
DO NOT MOVE!

07:41.495 --> 07:42.196
OH, MY.
[ MUTTERS ]

07:42.229 --> 07:43.830
YOU, TOO,
OLD PEOPLE.

07:43.864 --> 07:44.798
TIPTON.

07:44.831 --> 07:47.100
WHAT DID HE SAY?
HE CALLED US OLD.

07:47.134 --> 07:49.002
THIS IS MY HOUSE.
I LIVE HERE.

07:49.036 --> 07:51.104
PUT THE GUN DOWN.
PUT IT DOWN, TIPTON.

07:51.138 --> 07:52.606
S‐SORRY ABOUT THAT,
FOLKS.

07:52.639 --> 07:53.974
COME ON.

07:54.007 --> 07:55.209
YOU NEED TO SEND SOME MEN
OVER TO HALCYON ROAD

07:55.242 --> 07:56.276
AND GET TIRE IMPRINTS.

07:56.310 --> 07:58.078
AND SHE WAS SHOT
FROM OVER THERE.

07:58.111 --> 07:59.546
THAT'S WHERE YOU NEED
TO LOOK FOR SHELL CASINGS,

07:59.580 --> 08:01.248
POTENTIAL HAIR SAMPLES,
FOOTPRINTS, FINGERPRINTS,

08:01.281 --> 08:03.417
ANYTHING YOU CAN COMPUTER‐CHECK
AGAINST KNOWN ‐‐

08:03.450 --> 08:05.452
ONE OF YOUR GUYS
IS STEPPING IN HER BLOOD.

08:05.485 --> 08:08.322
OH, SHIT!
SON, HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
A RIDE TO THE HOSPITAL?

08:08.355 --> 08:10.991
I'M SURE YOU'D LIKE TO SEE
HOW YOUR MOTHER'S DOING.

08:11.024 --> 08:12.826
I'M HAPPY TO ZIP YOU
RIGHT OVER THERE

08:12.860 --> 08:14.027
WHILE THE MEN HERE
LOOK AROUND.

08:14.061 --> 08:15.696
JESUS. FINE.

08:15.729 --> 08:16.763
PLEASE TAKE ME TO THE HOSPITAL

08:16.797 --> 08:18.031
SO I DON'T HAVE TO WATCH
YOU GUYS

08:18.065 --> 08:19.466
FUCK UP THE CRIME SCENE
ANYMORE.

08:19.499 --> 08:20.567
I'M WATCHING YOU, KID.

08:20.601 --> 08:22.803
GOOD. WATCH THIS.

08:22.836 --> 08:24.638
WE'RE GOING.
TIPTON, YOU'RE IN CHARGE.

08:24.671 --> 08:25.539
WHERE ARE
THEY GOING?

08:25.572 --> 08:26.373
MESSY TYPES, FOR SURE.

08:26.406 --> 08:27.508
MESSY.

08:34.715 --> 08:35.716
CAN I
GET A COFFEE?

08:36.984 --> 08:38.018
SHE GETS COFFEE?

08:38.051 --> 08:38.819
I WANT FLAN.

08:38.852 --> 08:41.221
GET WHATEVER YOU WANT.

08:41.255 --> 08:43.190
WATCH TV. KEEP YOUR PHONES ON.
DO NOT WANDER.

08:43.223 --> 08:45.158
STAY IN THE CAFETERIA,
OR YOU COME BACK HERE.

08:47.094 --> 08:48.829
OKAY, IT'S GOT TO BE
THE MEXICANS, RIGHT?

08:48.862 --> 08:51.198
SURE. MEXICANS.
WHY NOT?

08:51.231 --> 08:52.799
DOES THAT MEAN
THEY'RE GONNA COME BACK ‐‐

08:52.833 --> 08:54.468
YOU KNOW,
TO FINISH THE JOB?

08:54.501 --> 08:55.669
UNLESS THEY <i>HAVE.</i>

08:55.702 --> 08:56.970
WOULD WE BURY HER
NEXT TO DAD?

08:57.004 --> 08:59.206
CAN'T. HE'S IN
A JEWISH CEMETERY.

08:59.239 --> 09:02.109
SHE DID CONVERSION CLASSES
BEFORE SILAS WAS BORN, REMEMBER?

09:02.142 --> 09:04.478
SHE NEVER ACTUALLY
FINISHED THEM, DID SHE?

09:04.511 --> 09:06.313
I DON'T KNOW.
I KNOW SHE TOOK THE CLASSES.

09:06.346 --> 09:08.782
MOM EATS CHEESEBURGERS
AND SHRIMP.

09:08.815 --> 09:10.150
WE'VE HAD CHRISTMAS TREES
EVERY YEAR.

09:10.184 --> 09:13.153
LIKE MOST JEWS.
MAYBE SHE DID CONVERT.

09:13.187 --> 09:15.756
BOTWIN FAMILY?
YES,
RIGHT HERE, YES.

09:15.789 --> 09:19.426
IS SHE ALIVE?
YES. HOWEVER,
SHE IS IN A COMA, AND, UH ‐‐

09:19.459 --> 09:20.694
I WON'T PULL THE PLUG.

09:20.727 --> 09:21.962
I WILL.

09:21.995 --> 09:24.531
I CAN DO THAT FOR HER.
SHE DID IT FOR BUBBIE.

09:24.565 --> 09:27.534
OH, NO, THE COMA IS MEDICALLY
INDUCED TO ARREST SWELLING.

09:27.568 --> 09:29.303
IF WE SEE THE SWELLING HAS COME
DOWN, WE'LL BRING HER OUT

09:29.336 --> 09:31.071
AND BETTER ASSESS WHERE WE ARE
IN TERMS OF BRAIN DAMAGE.

09:31.104 --> 09:33.240
HOW LONG
DOES THAT TAKE?
WE DON'T KNOW YET.

09:33.273 --> 09:35.943
YOU DIDN'T USE THAT
MICHAEL JACKSON DRUG, DID YOU?

09:35.976 --> 09:38.045
'CAUSE THAT DIDN'T TURN OUT
TOO WELL.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.013
PROPOFOL, WHEN PROPERLY
ADMINISTERED AND MONITORED,

09:40.047 --> 09:41.014
IS A SAFE DRUG.

09:41.048 --> 09:42.049
I DON'T KNOW.

09:42.082 --> 09:44.117
I HAD SOME
FOR A COLONOSCOPY ONCE,

09:44.151 --> 09:46.286
AND, PHEW, CRAZY DREAMS ‐‐
MONKEYS FISTING ME.

09:46.320 --> 09:48.222
I MEAN, THAT'S KIND OF WEIRD,
RIGHT?

09:48.255 --> 09:51.191
IF YOU'D LIKE TO SEE HER,
YOU CAN GO IN ONE AT A TIME.

09:51.225 --> 09:52.559
DID SHE SAY ANYTHING?

09:52.593 --> 09:54.895
BEFORE YOU PUT HER IN THE COMA,
WAS SHE TALKING AGAIN?

09:54.928 --> 09:56.663
YES, SHE WAS,
AND THAT'S A GOOD SIGN.

09:56.697 --> 09:59.333
WHAT DID SHE SAY?
DID SHE MENTION THE NAME ANDY?

09:59.366 --> 10:03.871
NO, SHE ONLY SAID THAT I HAD
VERY PRETTY EYELASHES.

10:03.904 --> 10:06.173
SHE'S RIGHT.
YOUR EYELASHES ARE QUITE LUSH.

10:06.206 --> 10:08.008
WHAT ABOUT
THE BULLET?
OH,
IT'S IN THERE.

10:08.041 --> 10:09.343
WE'RE GONNA
LEAVE IT IN FOR NOW.

10:09.376 --> 10:10.944
SO,
WHO'D LIKE TO SEE HER?

10:10.978 --> 10:12.346
Both:
I'LL GO FIRST.
YOU GO FIRST.

10:12.379 --> 10:15.682
THAT'S RIGHT, YEAH.
GO AHEAD.
THIS WAY.

10:15.716 --> 10:17.384
HELLO,
BOTWIN FAMILY.

10:17.417 --> 10:20.087
I'M MRS. TAFT,
HOSPITAL ADMINISTRATION.

10:20.120 --> 10:21.955
SO SORRY FOR YOUR SITUATION

10:21.989 --> 10:24.725
AND SO SORRY TO BE
CLOBBERING YOU WITH THIS NOW,

10:24.758 --> 10:27.528
BUT WE ARE A PRIVATE HOSPITAL
AND BLAH, BLAH.

10:27.561 --> 10:28.996
HOW WILL YOU BE PAYING?

10:29.029 --> 10:31.899
I HAVE FORMS.
THEY NEED TO BE FILLED OUT.

10:31.932 --> 10:34.201
WE'RE NOT CANADA.
WE'RE NOT FRANCE.

10:34.234 --> 10:37.204
WE'RE NOT TAIWAN, COSTA RICA,
IRAQ, OMAN, SRI LANKA,

10:37.237 --> 10:40.874
ARGENTINA, NEW ZEALAND, SPAIN,
IRELAND, ISRAEL, PORTUGAL,

10:40.908 --> 10:44.278
GERMANY, UKRAINE, CHINA ‐‐
YOU GET THE POINT.

10:44.311 --> 10:47.548
WE'RE AMERICA.
WE TAKE ALL CREDIT CARDS.

10:47.581 --> 10:49.416
WHO GETS THE CLIPBOARD?

10:49.449 --> 10:51.652
Jill: GEE, WHICH ONE OF US
ISN'T BROKE?

10:51.685 --> 10:53.754
I SPY
WITH MY LITTLE EYE

10:53.787 --> 10:57.824
A TALL WALL STREET ANIMAL
WITH A CORPORATE CREDIT CARD.

10:57.858 --> 10:58.959
HERE YOU GO.

10:58.992 --> 11:00.427
AND AGAIN, SO SORRY
FOR YOUR SITUATION,

11:00.460 --> 11:02.596
AND IF THERE'S ANYTHING
I CAN DO ‐‐ LLEWELYN?

11:02.629 --> 11:04.064
Lleweln:
RIGHT HERE.

11:04.097 --> 11:06.400
AH. I'M MRS. TAFT.
SO SORRY FOR YOUR SITUATION.

11:06.433 --> 11:07.401
SHANE!

11:07.434 --> 11:08.936
WHO DID IT?
DID YOU CATCH HIM?

11:08.969 --> 11:10.704
WHAT THE FUCK IS WRONG
WITH YOUR CHILDREN?

11:10.737 --> 11:14.875
SHIT.
I'M GONNA KILL HER.

11:14.908 --> 11:18.579
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

11:18.612 --> 11:21.048
[ RESPIRATOR HISSING ]

11:24.885 --> 11:25.953
HEY.

11:25.986 --> 11:28.255
OH. HEY. WHERE THE HELL
HAVE YOU BEEN?

11:28.288 --> 11:30.324
WHERE'D YOU
GET THOSE?

11:30.357 --> 11:32.626
LEE R. CRAWFORD.

11:32.659 --> 11:34.928
HE HAS MANY FRIENDS.
THEY ALL HOPE HE GETS WELL SOON.

11:34.962 --> 11:36.330
SNACK THIEF.

11:36.363 --> 11:38.732
YEAH, WELL, MY DINNER
WAS RUDELY INTERRUPTED.

11:38.765 --> 11:40.133
YEAH,
I'M KIND OF HUNGRY, TOO.

11:40.167 --> 11:41.902
FROM ALL THAT RUNNING
IN THE WOODS?

11:41.935 --> 11:42.970
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:43.003 --> 11:45.105
THERE'S TAPENADE
AND FANCY CRACKERS.

11:45.138 --> 11:47.207
PULL HER CURTAIN
IN CASE SOMEONE COMES IN.

11:47.241 --> 11:48.141
MM.

11:48.175 --> 11:50.744
WOW.
YOU WENT TO TOWN.

11:50.777 --> 11:52.713
HE'S GETTING EVERYTHING HE NEEDS
THROUGH A TUBE, ANYWAYS.

11:55.415 --> 11:58.085
DID NOT SEE
THIS ONE COMING, HUH?

11:58.118 --> 12:00.287
COME ON. IT WAS ALWAYS
IN THE BACK OF OUR MINDS.

12:00.320 --> 12:03.624
WHAT WOULD YOU HAVE DONE IF YOU
WOULD HAVE CAUGHT UP WITH HIM?

12:03.657 --> 12:05.125
HE HAD
A FUCKING RIFLE.

12:05.158 --> 12:06.827
I KNOW
HOW TO DISARM SOMEONE.

12:06.860 --> 12:09.062
BULLSHIT.
I DO.
WE LEARNED IT LAST WEEK.

12:09.096 --> 12:10.297
YOU LEARNED <i>WHAT?</i>

12:10.330 --> 12:12.132
HOW TO SUBDUE AND DISARM
A SUSPECT.

12:12.165 --> 12:14.768
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

12:14.801 --> 12:16.370
I'M IN
THE POLICE ACADEMY.

12:16.403 --> 12:19.540
[ LAUGHS ]

12:19.573 --> 12:21.341
THAT'S FUNNY.
I'M SERIOUS.

12:21.375 --> 12:22.943
I'M IN
THE POLICE ACADEMY.

12:22.976 --> 12:24.044
I'M NOT IN COLLEGE.

12:24.077 --> 12:25.979
THAT'S WHERE I GO
EVERY DAY.

12:28.182 --> 12:32.119
SHANE...
WE'RE...CRIMINALS.

12:32.152 --> 12:35.656
IT'S THE FAMILY BUSINESS.
WHAT THE FUCK ARE YOU DOING?

12:35.689 --> 12:36.990
I HAD TO.

12:37.024 --> 12:38.525
IT WAS THIS WHOLE THING
WITH OUELLETTE.

12:38.559 --> 12:40.794
THE WEIRD PART IS
I KIND OF LIKE IT,

12:40.827 --> 12:42.496
AND I THINK
I WANT TO BE A COP.

12:43.897 --> 12:46.300
THAT'S BAT‐SHIT CRAZY.

12:46.333 --> 12:48.502
I'M HOPING THEY'LL
LET ME USE A CROQUET MALLET

12:48.535 --> 12:49.937
INSTEAD OF A BILLY CLUB.

12:49.970 --> 12:51.071
DON'T TELL MOM.

12:51.104 --> 12:53.207
[ Chuckling ]
JESUS, WHAT AM I SAYING?

12:53.240 --> 12:56.210
WHO KNOWS?
MAYBE SHE'S HEARING EVERYTHING.

12:56.243 --> 13:00.247
[ CHUCKLES ] HEY, MOM, ANY IDEA
WHO SHOT YOU IN THE HEAD?

13:00.280 --> 13:02.683
ANY GUESSES?

13:02.716 --> 13:04.785
DO YOU HAVE
ANY GUESSES?

13:04.818 --> 13:06.086
GUILLERMO? CESAR?

13:06.119 --> 13:08.522
ANY OTHER
RANDOM MEXICAN GANGSTER?

13:08.555 --> 13:11.124
WELL, WHAT ABOUT
THAT CRAZY LESBIAN, UM...

13:11.158 --> 13:12.292
WHAT WAS HER NAME?

13:12.326 --> 13:16.129
ZOYA?
WHAT ABOUT ZOYA?
CRIME OF PASSION?

13:16.163 --> 13:17.965
IT'S NOT HER M.O.
SHE'S AN ARSONIST.

13:17.998 --> 13:19.833
SHE WOULD HAVE GONE
ALL JOAN OF ARC ON MOM.

13:19.867 --> 13:21.768
HOW ABOUT
YOUR GIRLFRIEND, EMMA?

13:21.802 --> 13:24.071
NANCY SCREWED HER UP
PRETTY BAD.

13:24.104 --> 13:26.006
NO,
I DOUBT IT WAS EMMA.

13:26.039 --> 13:27.574
WARREN SCHIFF?

13:27.608 --> 13:30.077
I THINK HE'S IN JAIL.

13:30.110 --> 13:31.979
WHAT ABOUT THAT CHICK
WHOSE HUSBAND NANCY BANGED

13:32.012 --> 13:33.380
IN THE TRAILER PARK?

13:33.413 --> 13:37.184
IT COULD BE BIKERS, ARMENIANS,
D. E. A. AGENTS GONE ROGUE.

13:37.217 --> 13:39.820
HEYLIA MIGHT HAVE FINALLY
GROWN SOME BALLS.

13:39.853 --> 13:41.955
THERE ARE
A LOT OF POSSIBILITIES.

13:41.989 --> 13:44.358
SHE'S SO GREAT
AT PISSING PEOPLE OFF.

13:47.528 --> 13:50.564
THINK HE'LL COME BACK,
TRY AND FINISH WHAT HE STARTED?

13:50.597 --> 13:52.032
I DON'T KNOW.
HOPE SO.

13:52.065 --> 13:54.468
GIVE ME A CHANCE
TO NAIL THE FUCKER.

13:57.104 --> 13:59.806
AND WHAT IF HE COMES BACK
TO FINISH WHAT HE STARTED?

13:59.840 --> 14:01.842
WHAT THEN?
SHE NEEDS SECURITY.

14:01.875 --> 14:04.344
THERE SHOULD BE A GUARD
POSTED AT HER DOOR.

14:04.378 --> 14:06.813
WE SHOULD HAVE SECURITY DETAIL
AT OUR HOUSE.

14:06.847 --> 14:08.916
SOMEBODY SHOT HER
IN THE HEAD.

14:08.949 --> 14:11.084
WE DON'T KNOW
THAT THE SHOOTER

14:11.118 --> 14:13.921
WAS SPECIFICALLY TARGETING
YOUR, UH, WIFE?

14:13.954 --> 14:15.222
UH, SISTER‐IN‐LAW,

14:15.255 --> 14:17.925
BUT THAT DOES NOT ADEQUATELY
EXPLAIN OUR RELATIONSHIP.

14:17.958 --> 14:20.561
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.
THE POINT IS YOU'RE WRONG.

14:20.594 --> 14:23.430
SHE WAS SPECIFICALLY TARGETED
FOR MANY, MANY REASONS

14:23.463 --> 14:25.566
THAT YOU CAN FIGURE OUT
FOR YOURSELF.

14:25.599 --> 14:26.967
SHE NEEDS PROTECTION.

14:27.000 --> 14:28.602
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
SIR, WITH ALL DUE RESPECT ‐‐

14:28.635 --> 14:30.304
Jill:
YOU THINK IT'S FUNNY?!

14:30.337 --> 14:32.472
YOU THINK THE WORLD
NEEDS TO SEE A PICTURE
OF MY SISTER LIKE THAT?

14:32.506 --> 14:34.408
YOU KNOW, I HEARD THAT THEY OWN
THAT PHOTO NOW.

14:34.441 --> 14:35.809
THEY COULD USE IT
FOR ADVERTISING.

14:35.843 --> 14:38.145
THEY DON'T OWN IT.
YES, THEY DO!

14:38.178 --> 14:41.048
YOU READ THE FINE PRINT
ON THAT SERVICE AGREEMENT.

14:41.081 --> 14:43.650
TAKE IT DOWN NOW.
WHERE'S YOUR PHONE?

14:43.684 --> 14:45.385
IT'S AT HOME.
OKAY. LET'S GO.

14:45.419 --> 14:46.353
Andy: NO.

14:46.386 --> 14:48.689
NO! YOU CANNOT GO HOME.
IT IS NOT SAFE THERE.

14:48.722 --> 14:51.358
PLEASE! SOMEONE'S
TRYING TO KILL NANCY, NOT US.

14:51.391 --> 14:54.795
SEE?
MA'AM, KINDLY LET GO
OF YOUR CHILD'S HAIR.

14:54.828 --> 14:57.297
HAIR? THIS IS A CLUMP OF DIRT
HANGING FROM HER HEAD.

14:57.331 --> 14:58.165
MA'AM.

14:58.198 --> 14:59.499
WILL YOU
PLEASE TELL HIM

14:59.533 --> 15:01.735
NANCY'S SHOOTING WAS NOT RANDOM
AND SHE NEEDS SECURITY?

15:01.768 --> 15:03.237
I NEED THE CAR KEYS.
DOUG HAS THEM.

15:03.270 --> 15:04.404
SHIT.

15:04.438 --> 15:05.539
OUT.

15:08.909 --> 15:11.044
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

15:14.715 --> 15:16.750
WHAT IF
SHE DOESN'T WAKE UP?

15:16.783 --> 15:18.919
FUCK YOU.
SHE'S GONNA WAKE UP.

15:18.952 --> 15:20.521
AND IF SHE'S RETARDED?

15:20.554 --> 15:21.688
[ DOOR OPENS ]

15:21.722 --> 15:23.924
OH. HEY, DOUG.
Doug: HEY.

15:23.957 --> 15:26.727
I BROUGHT FOOD
FROM THE VENDING MACHINE.

15:26.760 --> 15:28.729
IT'S ALL KIND OF CRAP,
BUT...

15:28.762 --> 15:30.564
THESE ARTICHOKE HEARTS?

15:30.597 --> 15:32.566
YOU MIND SITTING WITH HER
FOR A FEW MINUTES?

15:32.599 --> 15:34.868
WE WANT TO CHECK IN WITH ANDY,
SEE IF THERE'S A PLAN.

15:34.902 --> 15:37.070
SURE. NO PROBLEM.

15:37.104 --> 15:40.440
HEY, NANCE.
ROUGH DAY, HUH?

15:40.474 --> 15:42.442
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

15:42.476 --> 15:44.978
MMM. I LOVE THESE.

15:45.012 --> 15:48.182
LOOK AT
ALL THIS GOOD STUFF.

15:48.215 --> 15:51.652
YOU GOT STROOPWAFELS,
TAPENADE.

15:51.685 --> 15:56.924
OOH,
OLIVE OIL CRACKERS. YUM.

15:56.957 --> 15:59.993
MM‐MM‐MMM!

16:00.027 --> 16:01.929
FEELS KIND OF WEIRD
EATING OFF YOUR BODY,

16:01.962 --> 16:03.230
ESPECIALLY WHEN
YOU'RE NOT NAKED.

16:03.263 --> 16:04.464
[ CHUCKLES ]
KIDDING.

16:04.498 --> 16:05.432
TELL YOU WHAT ‐‐

16:05.465 --> 16:07.968
I'M GONNA MOVE THESE
ONTO YOUR TABLE HERE.

16:08.001 --> 16:11.939
THERE YOU GO.

16:11.972 --> 16:14.241
OH, SORRY. GOT ALL KINDS
OF CRUMBS ALL OVER YOU.

16:14.274 --> 16:15.676
LET ME WIPE THOSE OFF
FOR YOU.

16:19.413 --> 16:21.915
YOU STAY IN PRETTY GOOD SHAPE,
DON'T YOU, NANCE?

16:21.949 --> 16:23.150
TRIM. FIT.

16:23.183 --> 16:25.385
DANA USED TO ZUMBA,
BUT THAT DOESN'T SEEM LIKE

16:25.419 --> 16:27.387
THAT WOULD BE SOMETHING
YOU'D LIKE TO DO.

16:27.421 --> 16:29.990
ALSO, DANA'S BOOBS
FALL DOWN INTO HER ARMPITS

16:30.023 --> 16:31.658
WHEN SHE LIES DOWN LIKE THAT,
BUT NOT YOU.

16:31.692 --> 16:33.160
YOU LOOK GREAT.

16:33.193 --> 16:35.429
OH, ANOTHER CRUMB HERE.
LET ME POP THAT OFF THERE.

16:35.462 --> 16:37.364
WHOOPS.

16:37.397 --> 16:40.133
THERE YOU GO.

16:42.736 --> 16:43.937
WOW.

16:43.971 --> 16:46.907
BOY, YOU ARE JUST A MESS,
AREN'T YOU?

16:46.940 --> 16:51.111
TELL YOU WHAT ‐‐
I'M GONNA LOOSEN YOUR GOWN

16:51.144 --> 16:54.448
TO JUST KIND OF SHAKE IT OUT
A LITTLE BIT.

16:54.481 --> 16:55.115
[ Sighing ]
WOW.

16:55.148 --> 16:56.984
I HAD THIS IMAGE IN MY HEAD.

16:57.017 --> 16:58.585
[ DOOR OPENS ]

16:58.619 --> 17:03.991
THERE. THAT'S BETTER ‐‐
NICE AND TIGHT, NICE AND TIGHT.

17:04.024 --> 17:05.626
[ LID CLINKING ]

17:09.496 --> 17:10.364
IS THAT ‐‐

17:10.397 --> 17:13.133
HAVE YOU BEEN STEALING
FROM OUR BASKETS?

17:14.501 --> 17:16.270
WHAT, THIS?

17:20.841 --> 17:22.609
[ DOOR OPENS ]

17:22.643 --> 17:25.312
FINALLY GOT THE KEYS.
UGH.

17:25.345 --> 17:29.049
APPARENTLY DOUG'S BEEN BANNED
FROM THE HOSPITAL.

17:29.082 --> 17:30.317
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED?

17:30.350 --> 17:31.919
NEVER MIND.
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

17:31.952 --> 17:34.721
I'M GONNA HEAD BACK TO THE HOUSE
AND BEAT MY DAUGHTER IN PRIVATE.

17:34.755 --> 17:35.722
DO YOU NEED ANYTHING?

17:35.756 --> 17:38.392
DON'T YOU WANT
TO TAKE A MOMENT?

17:38.425 --> 17:39.459
NO, I DON'T.

17:39.493 --> 17:43.363
MAYBE WHEN SHE'S AWAKE
TO DEFEND HERSELF.

17:43.397 --> 17:44.631
I'M MAD AT HER.

17:44.665 --> 17:45.999
FOR GETTING SHOT?

17:46.033 --> 17:48.869
SURE.
ADD THAT TO THE LIST.

17:48.902 --> 17:51.705
SHE LOOKS
VERY PEACEFUL.

17:51.738 --> 17:52.940
WELL,
OF COURSE SHE DOES.

17:52.973 --> 17:54.541
SHE DOESN'T HAVE TO DEAL
WITH ALL THIS SHIT. WE DO.

17:54.575 --> 17:56.143
SHE GETS TO SLEEP.

17:56.176 --> 17:58.045
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:58.078 --> 18:02.883
SHE LOOKS DRY.

18:02.916 --> 18:05.219
EYE CREAM
IS VERY IMPORTANT TO HER.

18:05.252 --> 18:08.522
OH, LOOK AT THAT.
YOU'RE DOING SOMETHING SWEET.

18:10.157 --> 18:12.826
I DO SWEET THINGS
ALL THE TIME.

18:12.860 --> 18:17.497
I'M JUST SORT OF GRACELESS ABOUT
IT, SO PEOPLE DON'T NOTICE.

18:17.531 --> 18:20.734
I'M MOSTLY, YOU KNOW,
A DO‐GOOD PERSON.

18:20.767 --> 18:21.969
YOU'RE RIGHT.

18:22.002 --> 18:24.371
YOU ARE.
YOU REALLY ARE.

18:26.073 --> 18:27.407
THANK YOU
FOR NOTICING.

18:27.441 --> 18:29.376
THIS IS SO SURREAL.

18:29.409 --> 18:30.511
IS IT?

18:30.544 --> 18:32.546
FOR ME IT IS.

18:34.348 --> 18:36.049
OH.

18:36.083 --> 18:39.052
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

18:40.587 --> 18:44.858
[ MOANING LIGHTLY ]

18:44.892 --> 18:45.692
WAIT. WAIT.

18:45.726 --> 18:47.060
WHAT? WE SHOULD STOP.

18:47.094 --> 18:48.195
WE SHOULD STOP, RIGHT?

18:48.228 --> 18:50.397
THIS IS TOO INAPPROPRIATE.
IT'S WRONG.

18:50.430 --> 18:51.765
NO.
WHAT?

18:51.798 --> 18:53.400
NO.
WE'RE WORKING SHIT OUT.
YEAH.

18:53.433 --> 18:55.235
AND WE'RE FULL OF EMOTION.
IT'S FINE.

18:55.269 --> 18:57.371
I JUST ‐‐ I HAVE TO TAKE OUT
MY WEIGHT.

18:57.404 --> 18:58.739
YOUR WHAT?

18:58.772 --> 19:02.242
I ‐‐ I HAD TWINS,
ANDY.
RIGHT.

19:02.276 --> 19:04.545
AND I'M TRYING TO REBUILD
MY PELVIC FLOOR.
UH‐HUH.

19:04.578 --> 19:05.779
I KEGEL AROUND IT.

19:05.812 --> 19:08.749
IT'S LIKE DOING REPS
FOR YOUR VAGINA.

19:08.782 --> 19:11.585
HOT.

19:11.618 --> 19:12.486
CAN I SEE?

19:12.519 --> 19:15.489
MM.

19:18.692 --> 19:20.060
OW.

19:24.598 --> 19:26.433
WOW.
OH, IT'S HEAVY.

19:26.466 --> 19:28.735
I'VE BEEN DOING IT FOR A WHILE.
I'M GETTING PRETTY BUFF.

19:28.769 --> 19:30.304
BUFF MUFF ‐‐
I LIKE IT.

19:30.337 --> 19:32.239
OH, YOU WILL.

19:34.007 --> 19:35.642
[ BOTH MOANING ]

19:35.676 --> 19:37.911
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

19:37.945 --> 19:40.914
WOW. WHATEVER YOU'RE DOING,
IT'S WORKING.

19:40.948 --> 19:42.182
THANK YOU.

19:42.216 --> 19:44.284
DO YOU FEEL BAD?
I FEEL A LITTLE BAD.

19:44.318 --> 19:46.954
I FEEL GREAT.
THANK YOU.

19:46.987 --> 19:49.356
NOW I'M GONNA GO HOME,
WHERE YOU SHOULD GO, TOO.

19:49.389 --> 19:51.491
TAKE A BREAK.
TAKE A SHOWER.

19:51.525 --> 19:54.127
COME BACK LATER.
SHE'LL STILL BE HERE.

19:54.161 --> 19:56.563
YEAH.
I DON'T KNOW IF IT'S SAFE.

19:56.597 --> 19:58.799
I'M NOT WORRIED.

19:58.832 --> 20:01.935
COME HOME
WHEN YOU'RE READY. MWAH.

20:01.969 --> 20:03.937
I'M GONNA ORDER PIZZA.

20:03.971 --> 20:05.439
OH!
EXCUSE ME.

20:05.472 --> 20:06.473
SORRY.

20:06.507 --> 20:09.009
[ INDISTINCT SPEAKING
OVER P. A. ]

20:09.042 --> 20:11.144
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

20:14.781 --> 20:19.253
[ UP‐TEMPO JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS ]

20:19.286 --> 20:21.855
OH. UH,
THAT'S A VAGINA WEIGHT.

20:21.889 --> 20:23.590
THANKS.
[ GRUNTS ]

20:23.624 --> 20:24.691
SHE'LL WANT THAT BACK.

20:24.725 --> 20:25.826
NURSE!

20:25.859 --> 20:28.662
MY FRIEND'S REBUILDING
HER PELVIC FLOOR.

20:32.232 --> 20:34.101
Man on P. A.:
<i>PEDIATRIC ONCOLOGY TO 463.</i>

20:34.134 --> 20:35.536
<i>PEDIATRIC ONCOLOGY TO 463.</i>

20:35.569 --> 20:36.570
YOU MIND IF I SIT?

20:36.603 --> 20:38.672
WHAT?
NO. SIT AWAY.

20:41.575 --> 20:43.443
DAVE.
ANDY.

20:43.477 --> 20:44.478
ANDY.

20:46.480 --> 20:48.015
YOU'RE NOT HUNGRY?

20:48.048 --> 20:50.284
IT'S
HOSPITAL CAFETERIA FOOD.

20:50.317 --> 20:53.954
THAT SOUPçON OF DEPRESSION
AND GRIEF YOU GET IN EVERY BITE?

20:53.987 --> 20:56.023
CAN'T QUITE TAKE IT ON
RIGHT NOW.

20:56.056 --> 20:57.357
THEY DO
A NICE TAPIOCA.

20:57.391 --> 20:59.826
YOU CAN BARELY TASTE
THE SADNESS.
COME ON.

20:59.860 --> 21:02.062
TAPIOCA
IS INHERENTLY SAD ‐‐

21:02.095 --> 21:05.232
DELICIOUS, I GRANT YOU,
BUT A SAD, SAD FOOD.

21:05.265 --> 21:06.066
MM.

21:07.568 --> 21:08.635
DO YOU WANT TO TALK?

21:09.703 --> 21:10.671
ABOUT WHAT?

21:10.704 --> 21:12.206
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

21:12.239 --> 21:15.876
OKAY. IS THIS HOW PEOPLE SPEAK
TO EACH OTHER IN HOSPITALS,

21:15.909 --> 21:17.644
OR ARE YOU
CRUISING ME?

21:17.678 --> 21:21.548
WHICH, IF YOU ARE, I GOT TO SAY
ORDERING TUNA WAS A BAD CALL,

21:21.582 --> 21:24.885
BUT KUDOS TO YOU FOR CREATIVITY
IN TERMS OF LOCALE,

21:24.918 --> 21:26.153
AND I GOT TO PASS.

21:26.186 --> 21:28.388
NO,
IT'S A HOSPITAL THING.

21:28.422 --> 21:29.256
I LIKE WOMEN.

21:29.289 --> 21:31.158
MM. ME, TOO.

21:31.191 --> 21:32.860
WHO ARE YOU HERE FOR?

21:32.893 --> 21:34.628
MY DEAD BROTHER'S WIFE.

21:34.661 --> 21:36.597
SHE MIGHT BE DYING
RIGHT NOW,

21:36.630 --> 21:40.467
AND SO I FUCKED HER SISTER
UP AGAINST THE WALL OF HER ROOM.

21:41.735 --> 21:43.303
WOW.
OH,
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW.

21:43.337 --> 21:46.406
HER SISTER'S BEEN WORKING OUT
WITH THESE VAGINA WEIGHTS.

21:46.440 --> 21:48.375
WOW.
WE FOOLED AROUND A WHILE AGO.

21:48.408 --> 21:49.610
IT WAS FINE AND ALL,

21:49.643 --> 21:52.179
BUT, MAN, NOW IT'S LIKE
DICK MASSAGE UP THERE.

21:52.212 --> 21:53.514
LIKE,
THERE'S THE IN AND OUT,

21:53.547 --> 21:55.249
BUT THERE'S ALSO
THIS SQUEEZING THING HAPPENING

21:55.282 --> 21:56.483
THAT'S SIMPLY DELIGHTFUL.

21:56.517 --> 21:58.552
AND I KNOW IT'S ALL
IN THE HEAT OF THE MOMENT,

21:58.585 --> 21:59.953
IN THE FACE OF A CRISIS ‐‐

21:59.987 --> 22:02.122
I CAN'T THINK OF ANOTHER CLICHé
RIGHT NOW ‐‐

22:02.155 --> 22:03.524
BUT WHAT IF
SHE DIES?

22:03.557 --> 22:06.727
WHAT DO WE ALL DO THEN? AND
HOW COME I DIDN'T KEEP HER SAFE?

22:06.760 --> 22:08.428
AND WHY DOESN'T
SHE LOVE ME BACK?

22:08.462 --> 22:11.198
AND WHY CAN'T I MOVE ON
WITH MY LIFE, MY OWN LIFE,

22:11.231 --> 22:13.700
NOT THE ONE WHERE I'M
THIS SATELLITE ORBITING HER SUN

22:13.734 --> 22:15.068
AND RAISING HER SONS?

22:15.102 --> 22:17.037
I HAVE NOTHING,
AND MY LIFE IS HALF OVER ‐‐

22:17.070 --> 22:18.539
MORE THAN HALF,
PROBABLY,

22:18.572 --> 22:20.807
'CAUSE I HAVE
HIGH GENETIC RISK FACTORS

22:20.841 --> 22:22.543
FOR HEART DISEASE
AND COLON CANCER.

22:22.576 --> 22:24.778
AND EVEN IF SHE DOES
LIVE, SHE'S BEEN SHOT
IN THE FUCKING HEAD.

22:24.811 --> 22:26.713
WHO'S SHE GONNA BE?

22:26.747 --> 22:29.783
AND IF I'VE BEEN DEFINING
MYSELF BY HER ALL THIS
TIME, WHO AM I GONNA BE?

22:29.816 --> 22:30.918
AND YOU DON'T CARE.

22:30.951 --> 22:32.686
EAT YOUR TUNA,
WHICH, I GOT TO SAY,

22:32.719 --> 22:33.954
WAS PROBABLY
THE RIGHT CHOICE,

22:33.987 --> 22:35.622
'CAUSE THIS LASAGNA
IS DISGUSTING.

22:35.656 --> 22:38.792
HOW DO YOU RUIN LASAGNA?
I'M GONNA...
[ HANDS BANG, PLATES RATTLE ]

22:38.825 --> 22:41.562
...QUIT TALKING NOW,
DRINK MY FANTA.

22:41.595 --> 22:44.798
I LIKE FANTA. IT REMINDS ME
OF SPRING BREAKS.

22:44.831 --> 22:46.033
WHAT?
YOU'RE SURE YOU'RE DONE?

22:46.066 --> 22:48.202
AH, COME ON. I STILL GOT
MOST OF MY SANDWICH LEFT.

22:48.235 --> 22:49.903
I'M SURE
YOU GOT STUFF TO DO.

22:49.937 --> 22:51.205
I MEAN,
WHO ARE YOU HERE FOR?

22:51.238 --> 22:53.640
HERE FOR?
AT THE HOSPITAL.
WHO ARE YOU VISITING?

22:53.674 --> 22:55.108
I'M NOT VISITING.

22:56.043 --> 22:57.244
CHAPLAIN.

22:57.277 --> 22:58.779
WELL, ACTUALLY,
I'M A RABBI,

22:58.812 --> 23:00.113
BUT I DO THE CHAPLAINCY
PART TIME.

23:00.147 --> 23:01.949
YOU KNOW, IT BRINGS IN
A LITTLE EXTRA CASH,

23:01.982 --> 23:03.350
AND IT EXPANDS
MY WORLD VIEW.

23:03.383 --> 23:05.586
HAVE YOU EVER SAT WITH
A GRIEVING SOUTHERN BAPTIST?

23:05.619 --> 23:08.555
BOY,
THEY KNOW HOW TO PRAY.

23:08.589 --> 23:09.957
PERFECT.
THAT'S PERFECT.

23:09.990 --> 23:11.959
I JUST ASKED A RABBI
IF HE WAS CRUISING ME.

23:11.992 --> 23:13.627
IT MIGHT HAVE MADE SENSE
IF I WAS A PRIEST, RIGHT?

23:13.660 --> 23:15.362
AND THE SISTER FUCKING.

23:15.395 --> 23:18.599
FUCKING. WHAT IS THIS FUCKING
THAT YOU SPEAK OF?

23:18.632 --> 23:19.867
I‐I'VE NEVER
HEARD OF IT.

23:19.900 --> 23:21.535
STOP.

23:21.568 --> 23:23.470
IT'S MY JOB.
I LISTEN.

23:23.504 --> 23:24.605
I'M NOT JUDGING.

23:24.638 --> 23:26.306
NO?

23:26.340 --> 23:28.876
WELL, MAYBE A LITTLE BIT,
BUT I KEEP IT TO MYSELF.

23:28.909 --> 23:30.844
ALTHOUGH
THE VAGINAL‐WEIGHT THING ‐‐

23:30.878 --> 23:32.145
THAT WAS VERY INTRIGUING.

23:32.179 --> 23:35.382
NOW, HOW IS A JEW
THE CHAPLAIN IN OLD SANDWICH?

23:35.415 --> 23:37.084
WE ALL TRADE OFF
AT THE LOCAL HOSPITALS ‐‐

23:37.117 --> 23:38.685
THE MINISTERS, THE RABBIS,
THE PRIESTS.

23:38.719 --> 23:41.221
I PERSONALLY HAVE A LITTLE
CONGREGATION IN GREENWICH ‐‐

23:41.255 --> 23:43.190
TEMPLE MISHKON SHALOM,
HOUSE OF PEACE.

23:43.223 --> 23:45.993
ALTHOUGH WITH THE FIGHTING
THAT GOES ON WITH THE BOARD ‐‐

23:46.026 --> 23:48.028
I DON'T KNOW
IF I BELIEVE IN GOD.

23:51.231 --> 23:52.699
WELL,
YOU'RE NOT ALONE IN THAT.

23:52.733 --> 23:54.168
I FEEL VERY ALONE.

23:54.201 --> 23:56.670
WHICH IS WHY A LOT OF PEOPLE
TURN TO GOD.

23:56.703 --> 23:58.105
IT'S THE WHOLE CONCEPT.

23:58.138 --> 24:00.574
IT MAKES THE WORLD
A LITTLE LESS LONELY,

24:00.607 --> 24:01.842
A LITTLE LESS SCARY.

24:01.875 --> 24:03.777
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT
LESS SCARY.

24:03.810 --> 24:05.312
GOD COMES
WITH A LOT OF SCARY.

24:05.345 --> 24:07.781
[ CHUCKLES ]
AND I HEAR YOU ‐‐

24:07.814 --> 24:10.184
ESPECIALLY
THE OLD TESTAMENT GOD.

24:10.217 --> 24:12.686
HE'S, UH ‐‐ WHEW!
HE'S A GANGSTER.

24:12.719 --> 24:15.756
JILL SAID THAT NANCY WOULD LIVE
BECAUSE THERE IS NO GOD.

24:15.789 --> 24:18.492
AND IF THERE IS A GOD,
SHE DIES?
OH, ABSOLUTELY.

24:18.525 --> 24:20.794
WITH ALL THE SHIT
THAT SHE'S PULLED? YEAH.

24:20.827 --> 24:23.096
YOU AND JILL
COULD BOTH BE WRONG.

24:23.130 --> 24:24.698
ARE WE? THEN TELL ME.
YOU'RE THE RABBI.

24:25.999 --> 24:26.967
I HAVE NO IDEA.

24:27.968 --> 24:28.836
GREAT.

24:28.869 --> 24:31.605
ANDY,
YOU WANT AN EASY ANSWER?

24:31.638 --> 24:35.642
GO JESUS. GO ALLAH.
GO ‐‐ GO ‐‐ GO ATHEIST.

24:35.676 --> 24:37.010
I'M A JEW.

24:37.044 --> 24:39.179
MY OBLIGATION IS TO WRESTLE.
IT'S TO ENGAGE.

24:39.213 --> 24:42.683
IT'S NOT JUST TO SIMPLY,
BLINDLY BELIEVE.

24:42.716 --> 24:44.952
I MEAN,
THAT'S HOW I SEE IT.

24:44.985 --> 24:48.188
WELL, MAYBE I'LL DECIDE
WHEN SHE WAKES UP.

24:48.222 --> 24:50.257
YEAH.

24:50.290 --> 24:53.427
AND MAYBE
YOU'LL NEVER DECIDE.

24:53.460 --> 24:57.531
I'M GONNA SAY A PRAYER
FOR YOUR NANCY JUST IN CASE,

24:57.564 --> 24:59.566
IF THAT'S OKAY WITH YOU.

25:01.869 --> 25:04.404
YEAH.
KNOCK YOURSELF OUT.

25:04.438 --> 25:05.939
[ DOOR OPENS ]

25:05.973 --> 25:08.742
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

25:08.775 --> 25:11.445
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

25:11.478 --> 25:13.547
[ SIGHS ]

25:19.553 --> 25:21.989
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

25:27.628 --> 25:30.130
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

25:30.163 --> 25:33.333
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

25:33.367 --> 25:36.270
I THOUGHT
I'D FEEL BETTER.

25:36.303 --> 25:38.105
BUT I DON'T.

25:38.138 --> 25:42.576
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

25:42.609 --> 25:44.178
[ BOTH GASP ]
OH! OH!

25:44.211 --> 25:46.146
UGH! GOD DAMN IT!
SORRY. SORRY.

25:46.180 --> 25:48.715
DAMN IT!
DAMN YOU FUCKING PEOPLE!

25:48.749 --> 25:51.685
I'VE HAD IT!
I'VE JUST HAD IT!

25:51.718 --> 25:54.454
HE'S SORRY.
LOOK AT THIS MESS.

25:54.488 --> 25:56.790
[ RAPID BEEPING ]

25:56.823 --> 25:59.493
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

25:59.526 --> 26:02.496
YEAH, WELL...KARMA.

26:07.167 --> 26:11.038
<i>BLUE TEAM TO I. C. U., PLEASE.</i>
<i>BLUE TEAM, I. C. U.</i>

26:11.071 --> 26:12.940
